Because the tread is a steel‑belted, inextensible loop, its arc length \(L_{\rm t}\) is a material constant.  The outer radius \(R_{\text{eff}}\) of the wheel is therefore not an independent variable but is fixed by the belt length:
\[
R_{\text{eff}} \;=\; \frac{L_{\rm t}}{2\pi}\; .
